  "prompt": "What do they call it when you get beat on a big play and you act injured in football?",
  "response": "In football, when a player pretends to be injured after getting beat on a big play, it's often referred to as \"flopping.\" This term is borrowed from other sports, like basketball and soccer, where players exaggerate injuries or contact to draw a penalty or gain an advantage. In the context of football, it can also be described as \"playing hurt\" or \"selling an injury,\" especially if the intent is to draw attention or sympathy. However, it's generally frowned upon as unsportsmanlike behavior.",
